page.title: 02 NORSEY WOODS
page.content: On the north-east edge of Billericay is a delightful woodland area called{NORSEY WOODS.} Most of the people who live next to them don't mind unwanted visitors,like foxes and falling trees. Of the people we interviewed 32% had dogs,which they took walking in{NORSEY WOODS.}People often{picnic}there using the tables provided. The picnic area is right next to the footpath and the carpark. There is also an information centre with a{log book,}where you can put your name and any comments. There is also information about the most common trees, and the wildlife you will find. In{NORSEY WOODS}there is a{nature {trail}you can follow to ensure that you see the most interesting flora and fauna. It is possible to arrange for the warden to show you around.
